# Frontend — rules

## Server vs Client Components

- **Default to Server Components**. A Client Component exists only
  when it needs: browser APIs, state, effects, event handlers, or
  context.
- `'use client'` at the top of the file. Never mid-file.
- Server Component → Client Component is allowed. Client → Server is
  not (Next enforces this).
- Don't `use client` a layout unless absolutely necessary (blows the
  entire subtree out of RSC).

## A11y — strict WCAG 2.1 AA

- CI runs Playwright a11y on every public page. **0 violations
  critical/serious** is the gate. Not "try to improve" — it's the bar.
- Every interactive element has a reachable name:
  - Form inputs have `<label htmlFor>` or `aria-label`.
  - Icon-only buttons have `aria-label` + visible `<span class="sr-only">`.
  - Links go somewhere meaningful; no `<a onClick>` placeholders.
- Color contrast: AA (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large). Tailwind palette
  in `tailwind.config.ts` has been tuned — use the design tokens, not
  ad-hoc hex.
- Keyboard trap test: every modal supports Esc, Tab cycles stay inside,
  focus returns to the trigger on close.
- `aria-live` for async status. Don't over-announce — only user-initiated
  async.

## CSP & nonce

- No inline `<script>`. If you need init code, use a module import.
- Inline `<style>` in JSX (`style={{...}}`) is OK — covered by our
  `style-src-attr 'unsafe-inline'` (documented exception).
- Never `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless the content is either
  constant at build time OR sanitized via DOMPurify.
- Third-party scripts (Sentry, analytics) must ship with a nonce or
  be loaded via `next/script` (which handles the nonce).

## Forms

- Always use a schema validator (Zod) + React Hook Form. Never
  hand-roll `onSubmit` handling for anything with > 2 fields.
- Server Actions handle submission (`'use server'`). Client-side
  validation is for UX; server-side validation is the truth.
- Display field-level errors with proper `aria-describedby` pointing
  to the error element, and `aria-invalid={true}` on the input.

## Icons

- Use `lucide-react`. Consistent 24×24 grid, 1.5px stroke.
- Never use emoji in UI text without fallback (our codebase avoids
  emojis in production UI per user directive).

## Loading & error states

- Every route has `loading.tsx` (streaming) and `error.tsx`. Don't
  leave RSC streams that land as a blank screen.
- Errors in Client Components use an ErrorBoundary. Server errors
  bubble to the nearest `error.tsx`.

## Anti-patterns

```tsx
// ❌ Icon-only button without label
<button onClick={del}><Trash /></button>

// ✅ Accessible
<button onClick={del} aria-label="Excluir item">
  <Trash aria-hidden="true" />
</button>

// ❌ Server-only API called in a client component
'use client'
import { supabaseServer } from '@/lib/supabase/server'  // breaks at runtime

// ✅ Client uses its own client OR a server action
'use client'
import { createBrowserClient } from '@/lib/supabase/browser'

// ❌ Inline script
<script>{`window.DATA = ${JSON.stringify(data)}`}</script>

// ✅ Pass as prop / use next/script
<Script src="/init.js" strategy="afterInteractive" />
```
